# Auth & Security

## JWT lifecycle (BR-AUTH-013)

| Token         | Lifetime | Storage (client)                                           |
|---------------|----------|------------------------------------------------------------|
| Access        | 24h      | Memory + AsyncStorage (mobile) / httpOnly cookie (web)     |
| Refresh       | 30d      | Secure storage. **Hash** before persisting in DB.          |
| OTP email     | 10m      | Server-side Redis                                          |
| OTP SMS       | 5m       | Server-side Redis                                          |
| Reset link    | 15m      | Server-side Redis                                          |

- Refresh token rotation on every use.
- Web inactivity > 30m → server denies refresh.

## Authorization — policies, NOT role strings

```csharp
// ✅ GOOD
[Authorize(Policy = Policies.CanVerifyReport)]

options.AddPolicy(Policies.CanVerifyReport,
    p => p.RequireRole("Officer", "Admin"));

// ❌ BAD
[Authorize(Roles = "Officer,Admin")]   // scattered role strings, hard to audit
```

## Password (BR-AUTH-005, BR-DAT-001)

- bcrypt cost ≥ 12.
- Strength regex: ≥ 8 chars, upper + lower + digit + special.
- Lockout after 5 failed logins / 15 min → 30 min lock (BR-AUTH-011).
- CAPTCHA from attempt 3.

## Rate limits (BR-SYS-004)

| Scope | Limit |
|-------|-------|
| Anonymous public API | 60 rpm/IP |
| Authenticated user | 300 rpm/user |
| Submit report | 5/h, 20/24h per Citizen (BR-REP-010) |
| Map refresh | 20/min/user (BR-MAP-012) |

Use ASP.NET Core 9 `RateLimiter` middleware + Redis sliding-window for per-feature limits.

## Logging — NEVER log PII at Information level

- ❌ `logger.LogInformation("User {Email} logged in", user.Email);`
- ✅ `logger.LogInformation("User {UserId} logged in", user.Id);`

PII to mask/exclude: email, phone, GPS detail, CCCD, full address.

## Image / EXIF (BR-AI-007, BR-REP-011)

- Strip EXIF GPS before sending to AI service.
- Keep encrypted EXIF for verification — accessible only via admin policy + audit log.

## Secrets management

- ❌ NEVER commit connection strings, JWT signing keys, S3 credentials, FCM keys.
- Dev → `dotnet user-secrets`.
- Staging/Prod → env vars or AWS Secrets Manager / Azure Key Vault.

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOptions<JwtOptions>()
    .Bind(builder.Configuration.GetSection("Jwt"))
    .ValidateDataAnnotations()
    .ValidateOnStart();
```

## Audit log (BR-ADM-010)

Sensitive actions go through `IAuditLogger` → `audit_logs` table. EF interceptor for entity changes; manual log for config changes. Retention 12 months (BR-DAT-002).
